<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0"/>
  <title>ADR Identification Report – Task 1</title>
  <style>
    * { box-sizing: border-box; margin: 0; padding: 0; }
    body {
      font-family: 'Segoe UI', Arial, sans-serif;
      background: #f0f4f8;
      color: #1a202c;
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    header {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #1a365d, #2b6cb0);
      color: white;
      padding: 36px 24px 28px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    header .tag {
      display: inline-block;
      background: #e53e3e;
      color: white;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 1.5px;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      padding: 4px 12px;
      border-radius: 4px;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    header h1 {
      font-size: 26px;
      font-weight: 800;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
    }
    header p {
      font-size: 13px;
      opacity: 0.8;
    }
    .container {
      max-width: 820px;
      margin: 32px auto;
      padding: 0 16px 48px;
    }
    .card {
      background: white;
      border-radius: 12px;
      padding: 24px 28px;
      margin-bottom: 20px;
      box-shadow: 0 2px 8px rgba(0,0,0,0.07);
    }
    .card h2 {
      font-size: 15px;
      font-weight: 700;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.8px;
      color: #2b6cb0;
      border-bottom: 2px solid #bee3f8;
      padding-bottom: 8px;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    .info-grid {
      display: grid;
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: 12px;
    }
    .info-item label {
      display: block;
      font-size: 11px;
      font-weight: 600;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      letter-spacing: 0.6px;
      color: #718096;
      margin-bottom: 3px;
    }
    .info-item span {
      font-size: 14px;
      color: #1a202c;
      font-weight: 500;
    }
    table {
      width: 100%;
      border-collapse: collapse;
      font-size: 14px;
    }
    th {
      background: #ebf8ff;
      color: #2c5282;
      font-weight: 700;
      padding: 10px 14px;
      text-align: left;
      border: 1px solid #bee3f8;
    }
    td {
      padding: 10px 14px;
      border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
      vertical-align: top;
    }
    tr:nth-child(even) td { background: #f7fafc; }
    .badge {
      display: inline-block;
      padding: 3px 10px;
      border-radius: 20px;
      font-size: 12px;
      font-weight: 600;
    }
    .badge-red { background: #fff5f5; color: #c53030; border: 1px solid #fc8181; }
    .badge-yellow { background: #fffff0; color: #b7791f; border: 1px solid #f6e05e; }
    .badge-green { background: #f0fff4; color: #276749; border: 1px solid #68d391; }
    .badge-blue { background: #ebf8ff; color: #2c5282; border: 1px solid #90cdf4; }
    .highlight-box {
      background: #fff5f5;
      border-left: 4px solid #e53e3e;
      padding: 14px 18px;
      border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    .highlight-box.green {
      background: #f0fff4;
      border-left-color: #38a169;
    }
    .highlight-box h3 {
      font-size: 13px;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 6px;
      color: #c53030;
    }
    .highlight-box.green h3 { color: #276749; }
    .highlight-box p, .highlight-box li {
      font-size: 13.5px;
      color: #4a5568;
    }
    .highlight-box ul { padding-left: 18px; }
    .scale-row {
      display: flex;
      gap: 8px;
      flex-wrap: wrap;
      margin-top: 10px;
    }
    .scale-item {
      flex: 1;
      min-width: 80px;
      text-align: center;
      border-radius: 8px;
      padding: 10px 8px;
      font-size: 12px;
    }
    .scale-item .score {
      font-size: 22px;
      font-weight: 800;
      display: block;
    }
    .scale-active { background: #2b6cb0; color: white; }
    .scale-inactive { background: #edf2f7; color: #a0aec0; }
    .conclusion-banner {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #276749, #38a169);
      color: white;
      border-radius: 10px;
      padding: 20px 24px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    .conclusion-banner h3 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 6px; }
    .conclusion-banner p { font-size: 13.5px; opacity: 0.9; }
    footer {
      text-align: center;
      font-size: 12px;
      color: #a0aec0;
      margin-top: 32px;
    }
    @media (max-width: 540px) {
      .info-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

<header>
  <div class="tag">Task 1 – ADR Identification</div>
  <h1>Adverse Drug Reaction Identification Report</h1>
  <p>VirtualWorks Pharmacovigilance Training &nbsp;|&nbsp; Submitted Report</p>
</header>

<div class="container">

  <!-- Patient Info -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Patient Information</h2>
    <div class="info-grid">
      <div class="info-item"><label>Patient</label><span>Female, 45 years</span></div>
      <div class="info-item"><label>Report Date</label><span>June 2025</span></div>
      <div class="info-item"><label>Task ID</label><span>task1</span></div>
      <div class="info-item"><label>Reporter</label><span>Student – B.Pharm (8th Sem)</span></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Presenting Symptoms -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Presenting Symptoms</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Symptom</th><th>Category</th><th>Onset</th><th>Severity</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Rash (skin eruption)</td>
          <td>Dermatological</td>
          <td>~3–5 days after drug start</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-red">Moderate</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Itching (pruritus)</td>
          <td>Dermatological</td>
          <td>Concurrent with rash</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Mild–Moderate</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Nausea</td>
          <td>Gastrointestinal</td>
          <td>Within 1–3 days of starting medication</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Mild</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Dizziness</td>
          <td>Neurological</td>
          <td>Within 1–3 days of starting medication</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Mild</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>

  <!-- Medication History -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Medication History &amp; Timeline</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Drug</th><th>Class</th><th>Duration</th><th>Dose/Frequency</th><th>ADR Likelihood</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Amoxicillin</strong></td>
          <td>Beta-lactam antibiotic</td>
          <td>Started 5 days ago</td>
          <td>Standard therapeutic dose</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-red">HIGH</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Paracetamol</td>
          <td>Analgesic / Antipyretic</td>
          <td>As needed (PRN)</td>
          <td>Standard dose</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-green">LOW</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div style="margin-top:16px">
      <div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#4a5568;margin-bottom:8px;">Timeline</div>
      <div style="display:flex;align-items:center;gap:0;font-size:12px;">
        <div style="background:#2b6cb0;color:white;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:8px 0 0 8px;font-weight:600;">Day 0<br/>Amoxicillin started</div>
        <div style="background:#e2e8f0;padding:8px 14px;color:#4a5568;">Day 1–3<br/>Nausea, Dizziness appear</div>
        <div style="background:#e53e3e;color:white;padding:8px 14px;">Day 3–5<br/>Rash &amp; Itching develop</div>
        <div style="background:#744210;color:white;padding:8px 14px;border-radius:0 8px 8px 0;">Day 5<br/>Patient reports reaction</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Causality Assessment -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Causality Assessment (WHO-UMC Scale)</h2>

    <div class="highlight-box">
      <h3>Suspected Drug: Amoxicillin</h3>
      <p>Amoxicillin is a well-known cause of skin rashes and hypersensitivity reactions (reported in 5–10% of users). The temporal relationship between starting the drug 5 days ago and the onset of rash, itching, nausea, and dizziness is consistent with a drug-induced adverse reaction.</p>
    </div>

    <table style="margin-bottom:14px">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Causality Criterion</th><th>Assessment</th><th>Justification</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Temporal relationship</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-green">✔ Present</span></td>
          <td>Symptoms appeared within days of starting Amoxicillin</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Known ADR pattern</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-green">✔ Confirmed</span></td>
          <td>Amoxicillin rash is a well-documented, common ADR</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Alternative explanation</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">None identified</span></td>
          <td>No other drugs, food allergies, or infections documented</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Dechallenge possible</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-blue">Recommended</span></td>
          <td>Stopping Amoxicillin expected to resolve symptoms</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Rechallenge data</td>
          <td><span class="badge badge-yellow">Not applicable</span></td>
          <td>Not performed (contraindicated for safety)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>

    <div style="font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#4a5568;margin-bottom:10px;">WHO-UMC Causality Score</div>
    <div class="scale-row">
      <div class="scale-item scale-inactive"><span class="score">1</span>Unlikely</div>
      <div class="scale-item scale-inactive"><span class="score">2</span>Conditional</div>
      <div class="scale-item scale-inactive"><span class="score">3</span>Possible</div>
      <div class="scale-item scale-active"><span class="score">4</span>Probable</div>
      <div class="scale-item scale-inactive"><span class="score">5</span>Certain</div>
    </div>
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:#718096;margin-top:8px;">Classification: <strong>Probable</strong> – consistent timeline, known ADR, no alternative cause identified</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Naranjo Score -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Naranjo Algorithm Score</h2>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Question</th><th>Score</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Are there previous conclusive reports on this reaction?</td><td>+1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Did the ADR appear after the suspected drug was administered?</td><td>+2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Did the ADR improve when the drug was discontinued?</td><td>+1 (expected)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Did the ADR reappear when the drug was re-administered?</td><td>0 (not done)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Are there alternative causes for the reaction?</td><td>0 (none found)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Did the reaction reappear when placebo was given?</td><td>0 (not done)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Was the drug detected in the blood at a toxic concentration?</td><td>0 (not tested)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Was the reaction more severe when the dose was increased?</td><td>0 (not assessed)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Did the patient have a similar reaction to the same/similar drug?</td><td>0 (unknown history)</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Was the adverse event confirmed by objective evidence?</td><td>+1</td></tr>
        <tr style="background:#ebf8ff;font-weight:700;"><td>Total Naranjo Score</td><td>5 → <span class="badge badge-blue">Probable ADR</span></td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p style="font-size:12px;color:#718096;margin-top:8px;">Score interpretation: ≥9 Definite | 5–8 Probable | 1–4 Possible | ≤0 Doubtful</p>
  </div>

  <!-- Recommendations -->
  <div class="card">
    <h2>Recommendations &amp; Management</h2>
    <div class="highlight-box green">
      <h3 style="color:#276749;">Recommended Actions</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Discontinue Amoxicillin</strong> immediately and switch to a non-beta-lactam antibiotic (e.g., Azithromycin) based on clinical indication.</li>
        <li>Prescribe <strong>antihistamines</strong> (e.g., Cetirizine 10 mg OD) for rash and pruritus relief.</li>
        <li>Monitor for progression to severe hypersensitivity reactions (e.g., anaphylaxis, Stevens-Johnson syndrome).</li>
        <li>Document penicillin/Amoxicillin allergy in the patient's medical records.</li>
        <li><strong>Report the ADR</strong> to the national pharmacovigilance program (e.g., PvPI in India / Yellow Card in UK).</li>
        <li>Counsel the patient to <strong>avoid all penicillin-class antibiotics</strong> in the future and carry an allergy card.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Conclusion -->
  <div class="conclusion-banner">
    <h3>✔ Conclusion: Drug-Related Adverse Reaction Confirmed</h3>
    <p>
      The patient's symptoms (rash, itching, nausea, dizziness) are <strong>probably caused by Amoxicillin</strong>
      based on temporal association, known ADR profile, and Naranjo score of 5.
      Paracetamol is unlikely to be the causative agent. Immediate discontinuation and allergy documentation are indicated.
    </p>
  </div>

  <footer style="margin-top:24px;">
    <p>ADR Identification Basics – Task 1 Report &nbsp;|&nbsp; VirtualWorks Student Dashboard</p>
    <p style="margin-top:4px;">Prepared by: B.Pharm Student &nbsp;|&nbsp; Learn. Analyze. Identify. Impact.</p>
  </footer>

</div>
</body>
</html>
